          "settings": {
            "question": "What methods do you use for blemish removal?",
            "answer": "<p>We use two highly effective methods depending on the type of blemish: <strong>Short Wave Diathermy (SWD)</strong> uses a fine probe and electrical current to cauterise the blemish — ideal for skin tags, thread veins, cherry angiomas, and spider naevi. <strong>CryoPen</strong> uses precise nitrous oxide cryotherapy to freeze the blemish — ideal for seborrheic warts, age spots, and verrucas.</p>"
          }
